  "time_ut": 1657261628,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0dab\u0dba \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dd6\u0dc4\u0d9c\u0dad \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"Everyone should be equal in debt restructuring\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mrs. Julie Chang, the American Ambassador to Sri Lanka, said that China or any other country should not give special consideration to Sri Lanka in debt restructuring and all parties that have given loans to Sri Lanka should be treated equally.",
        "American Ambassador Mrs. Julie Chang said that the only solution available to recover from the current economic crisis in Sri Lanka is to get the support of the International Monetary Fund.",
        "She mentioned that it is something that not only the United States of America, the international community, but even the Sri Lankan people believe in.",
        "Mrs. Julie Chang stated that not only America, Japan and India but also the international community as well as economists recommended that Sri Lanka should get the support of the International Monetary Fund at the beginning of the current economic crisis in Sri Lanka and Sri Lanka was late in getting the support of the International Monetary Fund.",
        "Mrs. Julie Chang said that the debt restructuring process and its transparency should not be done just because the International Monetary Fund recommends it, and it will also benefit Sri Lanka.",
        "Mrs. Julie Chung stated that it will be very difficult for Sri Lanka to implement the policies and decisions they recommend to support the International Monetary Fund. She noted that implementing the recommendations of the International Monetary Fund is a difficult task not only for Sri Lanka but for any country in the world.",
        "Ms. Julie Chang said that Sri Lanka, as bilateral partners of the International Monetary Fund and the United States of America, should take care to protect the vulnerable people as well as the poor in implementing those recommendations. That is why humanitarian assistance is important to Sri Lanka. did",
        "Ms. Julie Chung said that the United States of America and Paris Club partners are supporting the recovery of Sri Lanka's economy. But she added that not only Western countries, Japan and India but also China should come forward to support Sri Lanka at this time.",
        "Ms. Julie Chung stated that the international community should decide what kind of assistance can be given to Sri Lanka and provide it. She also stated that assistance should be given to the parties that have given loans to Sri Lanka to restructure their debt."
      ],
